Atiku Abubakar, presidential candidate of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has visited party members who also contested the presidential ticket. Abubakar, who clinched the party’s ticket on Saturday, visited Nyesom Wike, Rivers governor, and former Senate President Bukola Saraki, on Monday. He also visited Anyim Pius Anyim, former senate president. According to the former vice-president, the visit is part of efforts to “strengthen cohesion” in the party ahead of the 2023 elections. See pictures below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-705883" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220530_181241.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="454" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220530_181241.jpg 732w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220530_181241-300x186.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220530_181241-24x15.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220530_181241-36x22.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220530_181241-48x30.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 732px) 100vw, 732px" />
